Diagnosis
. Right paraproct with a conspicuous digital process (
Fig. 36
). Via wide and strongly curved (
Fig. 41
). R1P ends distally as an expanded quadrangular area that includes the inner convex scale zone sz placed as in figures 40, 43 and 73.

Female
. Measurements in mm. N= 35. PL: 3.605‾.44; TeL: 2.06‾3.40; TL: 9.90‾18.71; IO: 1.50‾1.80; IOc: 0.90‾1.40; IA: 0.90‾1.40. Compound eyes with an acute ventral shape and a bigger interocular distance. Ocelli smaller than males widely separated. Brachypterous, tegminae present as lateral lobes, do not reach the metanotum. Wings absent. Genitalia as described for the genus (
Figs. 52–54
): the cerci bases are surrounded by TX laterally and followed by TIX (
Figs 52–53
). Tergal extensions of tergites VIII and IX are in contact with gonocoxa VIII (first valvifer + basivalvula) (
Fig. 53
). Gonangulum articulates with the tergal projections and the lateral part of the posterior lobe of second valvifer ring (
Klass, 1998
) (
Fig.53
). The three pair of valves are observed internally (
Fig. 52
). The ventral chamber wall is covered by a membranous cuticle with folds (
Fig. 52
). To see the spermathecal plate, the laterosternal shelf and the vestibular sclerite it was necessary to perform a dissection (
Fig. 54
).
